        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Sat night &#91;Hebrew&#93; 9&#45;1&#45;88<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">313 W 30</hi><lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>At a meeting of the<lb/> Trustees last Thursday night&#44; I was &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> to ask you to come on to confer with my father&#44;<lb/> Dr Kohut&#44; my brother&#44; Dr Drachman&#44; Rev Mr. de<lb/> Sola and prepare plan for College or educational<lb/> institute to submit to joint meeting of trustees<lb/> of these congregations or general meeting&#45;&#45;<lb/> of people interested in the movement&#45;&#45;whichever<lb/> shall seem the more desirable.<lb/></p>
            <p>I spoke a couple of weeks ago to Mr Jacob&#58; he<lb/> will not join us.  I called at Dr Kohuts Thursday<lb/>&#45;&#45;but could not see him.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev de Sola will be on in a fortnight&#45;&#45;he was<lb/> coming anyhow&#45;&#45;I will write to try and<lb/> hurry him.  Our congregation defrays<lb/> travel expenses&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>The resolution of the trustees was also to the<lb/> effect that you should be asked to invite<lb/> any Philad<hi rend="sup">a</hi> ministers you desired.  With regards<lb/> Hastily yrs H Pereira Mendes.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
